1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:01,835
[gunshot]

2
00:00:01,918 --> 00:00:04,504
[Azuelo] <i>It has been verified</i>
<i>by Jalil Abubakar</i>

3
00:00:04,587 --> 00:00:09,050
<i>that Domingo is among</i>
<i>the traitors in our ranks!</i>

4
00:00:09,134 --> 00:00:11,344
<i>The mission before you is to arrest</i>

5
00:00:11,428 --> 00:00:14,222
<i>SPO4 Felix Domingo!</i>

6
00:00:14,305 --> 00:00:15,890
[Suarez, in English] <i>Alpha to Base.</i>
<i>Target's missing.</i>

7
00:00:15,974 --> 00:00:17,642
Go into hiding. Don't let them catch you.

8
00:00:17,726 --> 00:00:20,145
Our plan isn't over yet.

9
00:00:20,228 --> 00:00:21,563
[Felix, in English] <i>Copy, General.</i>

10
00:00:24,983 --> 00:00:27,193
[Azuelo] <i>My condolences to your family,</i>

11
00:00:28,528 --> 00:00:30,613
<i>Jalil Abubakar.</i>

12
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:34,743
[Marcus] <i>I will solve this case.</i>

13
00:00:35,410 --> 00:00:37,412
<i>I will clear your name, brother.</i>

14
00:00:37,495 --> 00:00:38,830
[in Tausug] Thank you, brother.

15
00:00:38,913 --> 00:00:41,166
Don't worry. You'll get out of here.

16
00:00:41,249 --> 00:00:44,461
[Villanueva] <i>You'll be taking custody</i>
<i>of Jalil Abubakar.</i>

17
00:00:44,544 --> 00:00:46,671
- [Usman] <i>What transfer?</i>
- [Montes] <i>Didn't they tell you?</i>

18
00:00:46,755 --> 00:00:48,047
[Montes] <i>I guess they think</i>
<i>you'll help him escape instead.</i>

19
00:00:48,131 --> 00:00:49,799
<i>Just like what you did with Datu Rahman.</i>

20
00:00:49,883 --> 00:00:53,303
[Jamilah] <i>Doctor Teresa,</i>
<i>I'm sorry for hiding it.</i>

21
00:00:53,386 --> 00:00:56,222
There's no need to get a DNA test now

22
00:00:56,306 --> 00:00:58,391
because you're correct.

23
00:00:58,475 --> 00:01:01,352
[Jamilah sobbing] <i>Jalil is Gabriel.</i>

24
00:01:01,436 --> 00:01:05,815
<i>My father got Jalil</i>
<i>when the ship exploded.</i>

25
00:01:06,399 --> 00:01:08,777
Buddy, they're going to kill Jalil.

26
00:01:08,860 --> 00:01:10,070
[Jamilah gasps]

27
00:01:12,322 --> 00:01:14,741
- [cop 1] <i>Why is the fire alarm blaring?</i>
- [cop 2] <i>Is there a fire?</i>

28
00:01:15,325 --> 00:01:16,451
- [cop] <i>What happened?</i>
- [coughs]

29
00:01:17,035 --> 00:01:17,827
[cop] <i>Hey!</i>

30
00:01:17,911 --> 00:01:20,830
[overlapping shouting, coughing]

31
00:01:20,914 --> 00:01:22,582
[groaning]

32
00:01:26,085 --> 00:01:27,712
[Jalil] What's going on?

33
00:01:27,796 --> 00:01:29,088
Let's go! They're going to kill you!

34
00:01:36,012 --> 00:01:42,519
[mysterious theme music playing]

35
00:01:51,861 --> 00:01:54,155
[stirring music playing]

36
00:01:54,739 --> 00:01:56,658
[Jalil] <i>I didn't just see you as a friend.</i>

37
00:01:57,742 --> 00:01:59,702
<i>I came to see you as my brother.</i>

38
00:02:02,497 --> 00:02:05,083
[Teresa] I'm just so happy
because it's like…

39
00:02:06,835 --> 00:02:10,547
it's been so long
since we had a meal together.

40
00:02:10,630 --> 00:02:12,507
‪[dramatic stinging]

41
00:02:12,590 --> 00:02:14,717
[Marcus] Brother! Brother, wake up!

42
00:02:18,304 --> 00:02:20,140
[Jalil] Brother… [heavy breathing]

43
00:02:27,856 --> 00:02:29,899
[Young Gabriel] Marcus! Wake up!

44
00:02:29,983 --> 00:02:31,985
[young Gabriel] <i>Wake up, Marcus!</i>

45
00:02:32,527 --> 00:02:33,987
<i>Marcus!</i>

46
00:02:35,655 --> 00:02:37,407
[Marcus] <i>Wait for me, Gabriel.</i>

47
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:38,950
<i>I'm on my way.</i>

48
00:02:39,617 --> 00:02:41,786
- [suspenseful music playing]
- [fire alarm blaring]

49
00:02:42,620 --> 00:02:43,872
[cop 1] Why's there a blackout?

50
00:02:43,955 --> 00:02:45,957
[cop 2] Why is the generator not working?

51
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:48,418
- [cop 2] Are we getting attacked?
- [cop 1] Let's check it out!

52
00:02:50,795 --> 00:02:52,422
[Madrid] Why are the lights still out?!

53
00:02:53,256 --> 00:02:54,090
Fix it immediately!

54
00:03:03,641 --> 00:03:05,184
[Usman] Let's go.

55
00:03:05,268 --> 00:03:06,311
[officer coughs]

56
00:03:06,394 --> 00:03:07,729
Espina!

57
00:03:11,274 --> 00:03:12,233
[Montes] He's gone!

58
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,194
Sabdani!

59
00:03:16,362 --> 00:03:17,405
Come on!

60
00:03:20,116 --> 00:03:21,367
You bastard!

61
00:03:23,912 --> 00:03:25,747
Thank you for saving me. [heavy breathing]

62
00:03:25,830 --> 00:03:27,081
You're welcome.

63
00:03:27,165 --> 00:03:28,541
I found out that they will kill you.

64
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:30,627
I didn't waste time
and got here to save you.

65
00:03:35,089 --> 00:03:35,924
Here.

66
00:03:38,927 --> 00:03:39,761
Here.

67
00:03:40,637 --> 00:03:41,638
Use this.

68
00:03:42,597 --> 00:03:44,098
You'll need this while you're hiding.

69
00:03:46,184 --> 00:03:47,518
Hold on. What about you?

70
00:03:47,602 --> 00:03:48,978
Don't worry about me.

71
00:03:49,062 --> 00:03:50,271
What matters is that you're safe.

72
00:03:50,355 --> 00:03:51,439
I can take care of myself.

73
00:03:51,522 --> 00:03:53,691
You need to continue
your mission for Mustapha.

74
00:03:54,275 --> 00:03:55,985
[in Arabic] May Allah reward you
with goodness.

75
00:03:58,821 --> 00:04:00,240
Thank you so much.

76
00:04:00,323 --> 00:04:01,449
Be careful.

77
00:04:01,532 --> 00:04:03,076
- Thank you.
- [Usman] Go.

78
00:04:03,159 --> 00:04:04,202
‪[heavy breathing]

79
00:04:06,621 --> 00:04:09,123
[alarm siren wailing]

80
00:04:10,083 --> 00:04:13,378
[Montes] We won't stop
until we catch Jalil Abubakar!

81
00:04:13,461 --> 00:04:15,213
You're an animal, Sabdani!

82
00:04:15,296 --> 00:04:17,257
[Montes] You let a criminal escape again!

83
00:04:17,340 --> 00:04:19,259
All because you're both Muslims!

84
00:04:19,342 --> 00:04:20,468
[grunts]

85
00:04:21,094 --> 00:04:23,972
[grunting and groaning]

86
00:04:25,765 --> 00:04:27,976
- You've let Datu Rahman escape before!
- [grunting]

87
00:04:28,059 --> 00:04:30,311
And now Jalil Abubakar, too?!

88
00:04:30,395 --> 00:04:31,562
- [officer] Stop it!
- [clamoring]

89
00:04:31,646 --> 00:04:33,856
- What are you doing?!
- What's this?!

90
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:35,024
[officer] Back off or you'll get hurt too!

91
00:04:35,108 --> 00:04:36,776
- [gun cocks]
- [Eve] Go on!

92
00:04:36,859 --> 00:04:38,361
- [gun cocks]
- Come on!

93
00:04:38,444 --> 00:04:40,363
- Try and hurt him.
- Go on!

94
00:04:40,947 --> 00:04:43,032
[footsteps approaching]

95
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:44,409
[Marcus] Is there a problem here?

96
00:04:45,743 --> 00:04:46,786
Hey!

97
00:04:47,453 --> 00:04:49,038
What's going on here?!

98
00:04:49,914 --> 00:04:50,790
General.

99
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:53,626
Sabdani here

100
00:04:54,502 --> 00:04:56,963
helped Jalil Abubakar escape!

101
00:04:57,046 --> 00:04:57,880
‪[dramatic sting]

102
00:05:06,306 --> 00:05:07,140
Sabdani.

103
00:05:08,266 --> 00:05:11,311
Is it true that you helped
Jalil Abubakar escape?

104
00:05:11,394 --> 00:05:13,521
[morose music playing]

105
00:05:13,604 --> 00:05:15,732
[slams table] Answer my question!

106
00:05:15,815 --> 00:05:18,609
Did you help Jalil Abubakar escape?!

107
00:05:19,986 --> 00:05:21,154
I didn't help him escape, sir.

108
00:05:22,155 --> 00:05:23,239
I saved his life.

109
00:05:24,699 --> 00:05:26,326
Because Montes was planning to kill him.

110
00:05:27,368 --> 00:05:28,703
What are you saying?

111
00:05:29,537 --> 00:05:30,913
You're crazy!

112
00:05:31,831 --> 00:05:34,500
If there was no ill intent
towards Jalil Abubakar,

113
00:05:35,793 --> 00:05:38,087
then why would they transfer him
in the middle of the night?

114
00:05:38,171 --> 00:05:41,424
[in English] What are you trying
to imply, Agent Reyes?

115
00:05:41,507 --> 00:05:43,968
[in English] That was
a very urgent matter.

116
00:05:44,552 --> 00:05:46,471
The higher-ups are being cautious

117
00:05:46,554 --> 00:05:48,639
because they suspect

118
00:05:48,723 --> 00:05:50,558
Jalil Abubakar is conspiring

119
00:05:50,641 --> 00:05:53,728
with someone from NLEA and SID.

120
00:05:55,396 --> 00:05:57,148
And that those people
would let him escape.

121
00:05:58,066 --> 00:06:00,318
See? That's what happened.

122
00:06:02,528 --> 00:06:03,529
Sabdani.

123
00:06:05,448 --> 00:06:07,366
[in English] You are hereby suspended

124
00:06:08,159 --> 00:06:10,036
pending further investigation.

125
00:06:15,625 --> 00:06:16,793
Sir.

126
00:06:16,876 --> 00:06:18,461
If following orders

127
00:06:18,544 --> 00:06:21,672
is just watching
an innocent person get killed,

128
00:06:22,924 --> 00:06:25,468
then I'd rather lose my badge, sir.

129
00:06:26,469 --> 00:06:27,553
I will never regret

130
00:06:28,554 --> 00:06:31,724
defending a fellow Muslim brother

131
00:06:32,683 --> 00:06:34,560
from a rotting justice system.

132
00:06:34,644 --> 00:06:36,187
["Maninindigan" by Marko Rudio playing]

133
00:06:36,270 --> 00:06:40,525
♪ <i>Today, the morning is gloomy</i> ♪

134
00:06:40,608 --> 00:06:43,277
♪ <i>Opening my eyes after a blink</i> ♪

135
00:06:43,361 --> 00:06:47,490
♪ <i>In the midst of terror</i>
<i>Will burn</i> ♪

136
00:06:47,573 --> 00:06:51,077
♪ <i>The throne a tyrant playing king</i> ♪

137
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:56,124
♪ <i>The crown will be reclaimed</i>
<i>And returned to its rightful place</i> ♪

138
00:06:56,207 --> 00:06:58,084
♪ <i>Everything has an end…</i> ♪

139
00:06:58,167 --> 00:06:59,168
Brother.

140
00:06:59,252 --> 00:07:00,336
[door slams shut]

141
00:07:01,337 --> 00:07:02,255
[Usman exhales]

142
00:07:03,506 --> 00:07:05,299
Thank you for what you did for Jalil.

143
00:07:07,093 --> 00:07:08,511
It got you suspended.

144
00:07:09,137 --> 00:07:10,763
I knew I did the right thing.

145
00:07:10,847 --> 00:07:12,223
I have no regrets, brother.

146
00:07:12,306 --> 00:07:16,727
[Marcus breathing deeply]

147
00:07:16,811 --> 00:07:17,937
[Usman] Why?

148
00:07:18,020 --> 00:07:19,230
Is there a problem?

149
00:07:21,524 --> 00:07:22,692
Brother…

150
00:07:24,694 --> 00:07:25,903
It's about Jalil.

151
00:07:27,822 --> 00:07:28,906
He is Gabriel.

152
00:07:29,449 --> 00:07:31,075
[dramatic sting]

153
00:07:33,703 --> 00:07:34,620
G-Gabriel?

154
00:07:36,664 --> 00:07:37,623
Your brother Gabriel?

155
00:07:42,795 --> 00:07:45,631
I'm glad you've found
your long-lost brother.

156
00:07:45,715 --> 00:07:47,008
[Suarez] Sabdani.

157
00:07:47,091 --> 00:07:48,676
We heard about what happened.

158
00:07:49,260 --> 00:07:50,470
Don't worry.

159
00:07:50,553 --> 00:07:51,888
We've got your back.

160
00:07:52,555 --> 00:07:53,431
No one will be left behind.

161
00:07:54,974 --> 00:07:56,184
We got you, sir.

162
00:07:57,226 --> 00:07:58,561
We're all in this together.

163
00:07:59,937 --> 00:08:01,022
Thank you.

164
00:08:10,531 --> 00:08:11,949
[thuds]

165
00:08:13,409 --> 00:08:14,410
[slams table]

166
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:19,665
Our enemies are still plotting.

167
00:08:19,749 --> 00:08:21,334
Days are slipping by.

168
00:08:21,417 --> 00:08:24,462
Who knows which one of us
will be gone next?

169
00:08:24,545 --> 00:08:28,466
Look at each other,

170
00:08:28,549 --> 00:08:29,634
take care of one another.

171
00:08:31,844 --> 00:08:33,596
Because this small group…

172
00:08:34,931 --> 00:08:37,558
We can only trust each other

173
00:08:38,059 --> 00:08:38,893
for now.

174
00:08:40,186 --> 00:08:43,314
♪ <i>Until you are all united, stand up…</i> ♪

175
00:08:43,397 --> 00:08:48,194
♪ <i>If the law is only for a select few</i> ♪

176
00:08:48,277 --> 00:08:52,031
♪ <i>And justice comes with a price</i> ♪

177
00:08:52,114 --> 00:08:54,700
<i>♪ I will not remain silent anymore</i>
<i>This has to stop ♪</i>

178
00:08:54,784 --> 00:08:59,664
<i>♪ I refuse to be used anymore</i>
<i>Enough is enough ♪</i>

179
00:09:00,248 --> 00:09:01,123
Sir.

180
00:09:02,542 --> 00:09:03,459
- [door clicks shut]
- What is it, Jardin?

181
00:09:03,543 --> 00:09:05,127
Malacañang issued an order.

182
00:09:05,711 --> 00:09:07,296
Shoot on sight for Jalil Abubakar.

183
00:09:08,172 --> 00:09:09,131
What?!

184
00:09:09,215 --> 00:09:10,258
[tense music playing]

185
00:09:10,341 --> 00:09:12,343
[kick lands, chair thuds]

186
00:09:20,893 --> 00:09:21,894
‪[dramatic swoosh]

187
00:09:23,771 --> 00:09:25,523
‪[dramatic swoosh]

188
00:09:26,274 --> 00:09:28,776
[Ahmad] <i>I'll get you inside NLEA</i>

189
00:09:28,859 --> 00:09:30,528
<i>as a liaison officer.</i>

190
00:09:30,611 --> 00:09:32,071
I want to know

191
00:09:32,154 --> 00:09:36,117
what's going on inside and outside

192
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:39,537
of NLEA and SID.

193
00:09:39,620 --> 00:09:41,247
Sir Mustapha…

194
00:09:43,249 --> 00:09:44,875
I'll finish your mission.

195
00:09:47,545 --> 00:09:49,880
I'll put an end to Carillo's wickedness.

196
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:53,134
I'll make sure that animal
pays for his crimes.

197
00:09:53,718 --> 00:09:56,971
I will give justice
to the death of my father3

198
00:09:59,682 --> 00:10:00,725
Lara's…

199
00:10:03,269 --> 00:10:05,855
and to our community on the island.

200
00:10:05,938 --> 00:10:09,692
And even the innocent lives
that he has destroyed.

201
00:10:10,901 --> 00:10:12,695
I will find that animal.

202
00:10:13,696 --> 00:10:17,074
[dramatic sting]

203
00:10:17,158 --> 00:10:18,242
[music stops]

204
00:10:18,326 --> 00:10:22,580
[stirring music playing]

205
00:10:23,331 --> 00:10:24,457
[Teresa sniffles]

206
00:10:33,799 --> 00:10:34,634
Doctor.

207
00:10:38,179 --> 00:10:39,013
Jamilah.

208
00:10:40,056 --> 00:10:42,725
Doctor, I just want to apologize…

209
00:10:44,727 --> 00:10:47,730
for hiding Jalil's true identity.

210
00:10:49,190 --> 00:10:52,777
I don't have the right
to deny you the chance

211
00:10:52,860 --> 00:10:54,236
to be with him.

212
00:10:54,820 --> 00:10:56,530
I'm sorry.

213
00:10:58,449 --> 00:10:59,283
Jamilah.

214
00:11:01,327 --> 00:11:04,121
I understand why you've done that.

215
00:11:04,705 --> 00:11:05,665
It's because

216
00:11:05,748 --> 00:11:07,875
you wanted to protect

217
00:11:08,709 --> 00:11:09,543
your brother.

218
00:11:11,337 --> 00:11:13,255
Because you love your brother,

219
00:11:13,756 --> 00:11:15,049
my son, Gabriel.

220
00:11:16,467 --> 00:11:18,761
And for that, I want to thank you.

221
00:11:18,844 --> 00:11:20,346
[music turns dramatic]

222
00:11:20,429 --> 00:11:22,890
I would also like to thank your father,

223
00:11:22,973 --> 00:11:24,683
Datu Rahman.

224
00:11:26,185 --> 00:11:28,312
[voice breaking] For saving Gabriel.

225
00:11:29,271 --> 00:11:30,523
[sniffles]

226
00:11:31,107 --> 00:11:32,900
And he gave him

227
00:11:33,734 --> 00:11:37,655
the love I couldn't give
during those times.

228
00:11:38,447 --> 00:11:40,616
But, Doc, I can tell you this. [sniffles]

229
00:11:40,699 --> 00:11:43,119
I never felt like I was missing something.

230
00:11:44,537 --> 00:11:48,124
I owe that to the family
who took care of me.

231
00:11:49,792 --> 00:11:52,002
When I first met Jalil… [sniffles]

232
00:11:52,086 --> 00:11:52,920
…I knew

233
00:11:54,255 --> 00:11:56,132
that he had a good heart.

234
00:11:59,385 --> 00:12:00,719
[Jalil] Thank you.

235
00:12:01,303 --> 00:12:04,390
Thank you so much.

236
00:12:04,473 --> 00:12:07,685
It's because Datu Rahman raised him well.

237
00:12:09,186 --> 00:12:11,981
And you showered him with love.

238
00:12:12,064 --> 00:12:15,860
[Teresa sobbing]

239
00:12:20,114 --> 00:12:21,532
[Teresa sniffles]

240
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:23,993
[Marcus] Ma!

241
00:12:25,202 --> 00:12:26,579
- M-Marcus.
- [Marcus] Jamilah.

242
00:12:26,662 --> 00:12:28,289
Marcus. [sobbing]

243
00:12:31,750 --> 00:12:33,878
- How are you? How's your brother?
- [Marcus inhales]

244
00:12:33,961 --> 00:12:35,546
Someone tried to kill him.

245
00:12:35,629 --> 00:12:38,132
- [Teresa] What?
- Luckily, he escaped.

246
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:41,802
But now the authorities are after him.

247
00:12:41,886 --> 00:12:45,806
- [Teresa breathing heavily]
- [music turns tense]

248
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:51,729
[phone vibrating]

249
00:12:55,733 --> 00:12:56,859
Hello?

250
00:12:57,985 --> 00:12:58,819
[Jalil] <i>Jamilah?</i>

251
00:12:58,903 --> 00:13:00,237
Jalil!

252
00:13:01,113 --> 00:13:02,740
Jalil, where are you?

253
00:13:02,823 --> 00:13:04,742
[Jamilah] <i>We're worried sick.</i>

254
00:13:05,493 --> 00:13:06,952
I can't tell you.

255
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:09,580
It's too dangerous.

256
00:13:10,456 --> 00:13:12,166
I just want to know how you're doing.

257
00:13:13,584 --> 00:13:14,710
But Jalil…

258
00:13:15,419 --> 00:13:16,629
Jamilah.

259
00:13:16,712 --> 00:13:17,546
‪[Jamilah sniffles]

260
00:13:20,841 --> 00:13:21,926
Bro.

261
00:13:23,219 --> 00:13:24,053
Gabriel.

262
00:13:27,973 --> 00:13:30,100
Gabriel, my son.

263
00:13:31,352 --> 00:13:32,311
[Teresa sobs]

264
00:13:32,394 --> 00:13:33,812
[Marcus] <i>Bro.</i>

265
00:13:33,896 --> 00:13:35,356
Tell me where you are.

266
00:13:36,065 --> 00:13:37,149
So I can protect you.

267
00:13:37,942 --> 00:13:40,694
We can't be seen together.

268
00:13:42,238 --> 00:13:43,656
[Jalil] <i>You'll also get in trouble.</i>

269
00:13:44,406 --> 00:13:46,659
If something happens to me. If…

270
00:13:46,742 --> 00:13:47,743
I die…

271
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:51,163
I want you to continue with the mission.

272
00:13:52,915 --> 00:13:55,668
This mission is more important
than my life.

273
00:13:59,505 --> 00:14:01,090
- Gabriel!
- [line disconnects]

274
00:14:01,173 --> 00:14:02,424
[Marcus] Gabriel!

275
00:14:04,718 --> 00:14:06,679
[gasping]

276
00:14:08,347 --> 00:14:09,515
[sniffles]

277
00:14:12,268 --> 00:14:13,602
[music fades]

278
00:14:15,396 --> 00:14:16,772
- Ma.
- [mom] Oh.

279
00:14:16,855 --> 00:14:17,856
Oh, hey, son.

280
00:14:18,524 --> 00:14:19,859
How are you?

281
00:14:19,942 --> 00:14:21,402
Have a seat. Eat with me.

282
00:14:21,485 --> 00:14:24,530
[mellow music playing]

283
00:14:29,577 --> 00:14:30,953
Where's your gun?

284
00:14:33,664 --> 00:14:35,124
Did you get suspended?

285
00:14:36,709 --> 00:14:38,586
- Ma--
- Shh!

286
00:14:40,004 --> 00:14:42,339
You don't have to explain.

287
00:14:43,465 --> 00:14:44,508
I know you well.

288
00:14:45,384 --> 00:14:46,343
Whatever happened,

289
00:14:46,427 --> 00:14:50,973
I'm sure you only did
what you thought was right.

290
00:14:51,891 --> 00:14:53,767
You are just like your father.

291
00:14:54,977 --> 00:14:56,812
If he were still alive,

292
00:14:56,896 --> 00:14:58,105
I'm sure

293
00:14:58,898 --> 00:15:00,691
he's very proud of you.

294
00:15:03,527 --> 00:15:04,737
Just like me.

295
00:15:12,328 --> 00:15:16,665
<i>The authorities are still after</i>
<i>the suspect, Jalil Abubakar.</i>

296
00:15:16,749 --> 00:15:18,208
<i>He was arrested yesterday</i>

297
00:15:18,292 --> 00:15:21,170
<i>because of multiple charges</i>

298
00:15:21,253 --> 00:15:24,715
<i>involving illegal weapons</i>
<i>and destabilization.</i>

299
00:15:24,798 --> 00:15:27,051
<i>But last night, he escaped</i>

300
00:15:27,134 --> 00:15:30,220
<i>from the National Law Enforcement Agency</i>
<i>holding cell.</i>

301
00:15:30,304 --> 00:15:33,724
<i>And because he is considered</i>
<i>armed and dangerous,</i>

302
00:15:33,807 --> 00:15:37,686
<i>he is now classified</i>
<i>as public enemy number one,</i>

303
00:15:37,770 --> 00:15:40,272
<i>with an order to be neutralized on sight.</i>

304
00:15:40,356 --> 00:15:41,190
JALIL ABUBAKAR REMAINS AT LARGE
OVER ILLEGAL ARMS, DESTABILIZATION

305
00:15:41,273 --> 00:15:47,488
[suspenseful music playing]

306
00:15:47,571 --> 00:15:48,572
[digital trilling]

307
00:15:48,656 --> 00:15:49,990
What's the update, Madrid?

308
00:15:50,074 --> 00:15:52,952
Have you found
where Jalil Abubakar is hiding?

309
00:15:54,161 --> 00:15:55,204
[in English] Yes, sir.

310
00:15:55,996 --> 00:15:59,249
The safe houses of Mustapha
you ordered me to monitor…

311
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:05,214
One of them has started showing
activity since last night.

312
00:16:05,297 --> 00:16:06,632
Last night?

313
00:16:06,715 --> 00:16:08,801
The same night Jalil escaped?

314
00:16:08,884 --> 00:16:10,678
[tracker pinging rapidly]

315
00:16:13,055 --> 00:16:17,101
[computer beeping, whirring]

316
00:16:17,184 --> 00:16:21,230
[Jalil] <i>You've gathered a lot</i>
<i>of evidence, Sir Mustapha.</i>

317
00:16:22,272 --> 00:16:24,566
<i>It's enough to pin Carillo</i>

318
00:16:24,650 --> 00:16:28,195
<i>for the crimes he's blaming</i>
<i>on me and my father.</i>

319
00:16:28,696 --> 00:16:31,323
<i>This is why they killed you.</i>

320
00:16:32,116 --> 00:16:33,367
[in English] Good job, Madrid.

321
00:16:38,163 --> 00:16:42,710
[line ringing]

322
00:16:43,252 --> 00:16:44,545
[in English] Hello, General.

323
00:16:45,045 --> 00:16:46,505
I have good news for you.

324
00:16:48,173 --> 00:16:51,135
It looks like we can finally
eliminate Jalil Abubakar.

325
00:16:53,429 --> 00:16:54,680
[gloomy music playing]

326
00:16:54,763 --> 00:16:57,349
[Marcus] Jamilah, what are you doing here?

327
00:16:58,350 --> 00:17:00,060
I sent you here myself,

328
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:02,688
so obviously I'm around.

329
00:17:02,771 --> 00:17:05,774
Jamilah, my search for Gabriel
is far too dangerous.

330
00:17:05,858 --> 00:17:07,234
I know.

331
00:17:07,985 --> 00:17:12,031
That's why I want to help,
because he's my brother.

332
00:17:12,114 --> 00:17:13,699
[sighs] Jamilah…

333
00:17:14,199 --> 00:17:15,284
He's my brother, too.

334
00:17:15,367 --> 00:17:18,078
But I know him better, Sir Marcus.

335
00:17:19,997 --> 00:17:21,123
[Ethan clears throat]

336
00:17:21,206 --> 00:17:23,584
Uh, Sir Marcus, Jamilah.

337
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:25,836
You both make a good point.

338
00:17:25,919 --> 00:17:28,505
Yes, it is dangerous,
so we need to work together.

339
00:17:29,423 --> 00:17:30,299
[Ethan chuckles awkwardly]

340
00:17:30,883 --> 00:17:32,092
Have some coffee.

341
00:17:33,635 --> 00:17:34,970
[door clicks shut]

342
00:17:36,346 --> 00:17:38,390
[Jamilah sighing]

343
00:17:39,641 --> 00:17:43,479
I was wondering where Jalil
could be hiding right now.

344
00:17:44,063 --> 00:17:48,525
At the safe house where
Sir Mustapha kept Father safe.

345
00:17:50,110 --> 00:17:52,988
How was your time at Sir Mustapha's place?

346
00:17:53,072 --> 00:17:55,449
It was nice, dear.

347
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:59,244
I was treated with kindness.

348
00:18:00,329 --> 00:18:04,541
I was able to pray,
since there's a mosque nearby.

349
00:18:04,625 --> 00:18:06,376
[dramatic sting]

350
00:18:17,554 --> 00:18:18,806
Jamilah.

351
00:18:19,473 --> 00:18:22,434
How can you be sure that Jalil would hide

352
00:18:22,518 --> 00:18:23,894
in Sir Mustapha's safe house?

353
00:18:23,977 --> 00:18:26,563
Sir Marcus, like I told you,

354
00:18:26,647 --> 00:18:28,148
I know Jalil too well.

355
00:18:28,732 --> 00:18:32,653
He wouldn't risk an unfamiliar place.

356
00:18:33,237 --> 00:18:37,783
He would only hide where he feels safe.

357
00:18:37,866 --> 00:18:38,700
‪[digital trilling]

358
00:18:43,705 --> 00:18:46,458
- [keyboard clacking]
- [computer chiming]

359
00:18:46,542 --> 00:18:49,002
[gentle music playing]

360
00:18:56,468 --> 00:18:57,845
[keyboard clacking]

361
00:18:58,554 --> 00:18:59,763
Go check that CCTV.

362
00:18:59,847 --> 00:19:01,306
Alright, sir.

363
00:19:01,390 --> 00:19:05,561
[tense music playing]

364
00:19:14,278 --> 00:19:15,320
They're on the move!

365
00:19:16,613 --> 00:19:18,073
They've tracked down Gabriel.

366
00:19:22,452 --> 00:19:26,707
[music intensifies]

367
00:19:53,442 --> 00:19:54,276
[device beeps]

368
00:19:58,363 --> 00:20:00,282
[suspenseful music playing]

369
00:20:15,339 --> 00:20:16,173
‪[music intensifies]

370
00:20:27,309 --> 00:20:28,769
[magazine clatters]

371
00:20:29,478 --> 00:20:30,979
[rapid gunfire]

372
00:20:32,522 --> 00:20:33,607
[gun cocking]

373
00:20:42,074 --> 00:20:44,952
[gunshots blasting]

374
00:20:45,035 --> 00:20:46,411
[gun clicks]

375
00:20:55,879 --> 00:20:57,172
Dear God…

376
00:20:58,590 --> 00:21:01,134
[sniffles] Watch over my sons.

377
00:21:02,552 --> 00:21:04,429
[Teresa sniffling]

378
00:21:12,062 --> 00:21:16,066
[rapid gunfire]

379
00:21:28,453 --> 00:21:29,496
[gunshots blasting]

380
00:21:29,579 --> 00:21:30,414
[gun clatters]

381
00:21:32,124 --> 00:21:36,378
[rapid gunfire]

382
00:21:39,381 --> 00:21:41,174
[gunshots blasting]

383
00:21:44,428 --> 00:21:49,433
["Maninindigan" by Marko Rudio playing]

384
00:22:09,286 --> 00:22:10,537
Gabriel…

385
00:22:12,873 --> 00:22:14,041
My brother…

386
00:22:16,209 --> 00:22:17,586
My brother Marcus.

387
00:22:19,379 --> 00:22:20,672
Just call me bro.

388
00:22:27,763 --> 00:22:29,639
I'll protect you, Gabriel.

389
00:22:30,724 --> 00:22:32,267
I'll protect you.

390
00:22:36,104 --> 00:22:37,939
This is all the evidence
Sir Mustapha collected.

391
00:22:38,023 --> 00:22:39,149
This is a lot.

392
00:22:39,941 --> 00:22:42,611
This is enough to bring Carillo down.

393
00:22:43,945 --> 00:22:45,697
Jalil Abubakar!

394
00:22:45,781 --> 00:22:46,990
- [gunshots blasting]
- [gasping]

395
00:22:47,074 --> 00:22:48,784
[tense music playing]

396
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:49,701
[tires screech]

397
00:22:49,785 --> 00:22:52,120
[rapid gunfire]

398
00:22:53,163 --> 00:22:55,707
- [gunshots blasting]
- [grunts]

399
00:23:00,504 --> 00:23:01,880
- [gunshots blasting]
- [Jalil grunts]

400
00:23:03,590 --> 00:23:04,466
Come on!

401
00:23:04,549 --> 00:23:05,884
Let's go, Gabriel!

402
00:23:05,967 --> 00:23:09,429
[rapid gunfire]

403
00:23:13,725 --> 00:23:15,602
[Marcus] Gabriel, get in!

404
00:23:17,312 --> 00:23:20,440
[gunshots blasting]

405
00:23:20,524 --> 00:23:22,025
[tires screeching]

406
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:35,163
[gloomy music playing]

407
00:23:36,581 --> 00:23:37,582
[Teresa] Jamilah…

408
00:23:38,708 --> 00:23:39,793
[Jamilah] Doctor…

409
00:23:40,877 --> 00:23:42,504
- Any updates?
- [exhales deeply]

410
00:23:42,587 --> 00:23:43,797
Doctor…

411
00:23:43,880 --> 00:23:45,048
Jalil…

412
00:23:45,132 --> 00:23:46,675
He was already found by Sir Marcus.

413
00:23:46,758 --> 00:23:48,093
[relieved sigh]

414
00:23:48,885 --> 00:23:50,512
I wonder where they might be
at this moment,

415
00:23:50,595 --> 00:23:52,097
and what's happening.

416
00:23:52,180 --> 00:23:53,932
[sighs]

417
00:23:54,015 --> 00:23:56,059
I hope they're both safe, Doctor.

418
00:23:56,685 --> 00:23:58,728
[reporter on TV] <i>In the latest news,</i>

419
00:23:58,812 --> 00:24:02,232
<i>the NLEA operatives have found the hideout</i>

420
00:24:02,315 --> 00:24:04,526
<i>of the suspect, Jalil Abubakar.</i>

421
00:24:04,609 --> 00:24:07,988
<i>Unfortunately, he managed</i>
<i>to escape once again,</i>

422
00:24:08,071 --> 00:24:10,574
<i>with the help of the Golden Boy</i>

423
00:24:10,657 --> 00:24:12,617
<i>of the Special Investigations Division,</i>

424
00:24:12,701 --> 00:24:14,536
<i>Agent Marcus Reyes.</i>

425
00:24:14,619 --> 00:24:19,666
<i>According to the report, the two</i>
<i>exchanged fire with the police.</i>

426
00:24:21,001 --> 00:24:22,794
[in English] Goddammit!

427
00:24:24,379 --> 00:24:26,673
Why is this happening to us?!

428
00:24:27,174 --> 00:24:28,466
[Felix] Well?

429
00:24:29,384 --> 00:24:30,802
What did I say?

430
00:24:32,095 --> 00:24:33,763
Those two are the real criminals,

431
00:24:33,847 --> 00:24:37,976
and yet you call me the traitor?!

432
00:24:38,059 --> 00:24:39,895
See what happened now!

433
00:24:40,437 --> 00:24:41,855
Say something!

434
00:24:44,774 --> 00:24:46,401
- [Felix] How dare you!
- You bastard!

435
00:24:46,484 --> 00:24:48,653
- Hey, stop this!
- Don't fight!

436
00:24:48,737 --> 00:24:50,071
- Please stop!
- Damn you!

437
00:24:50,155 --> 00:24:51,573
- Come on, pull it out!
- [officer] Calm down!

438
00:24:51,656 --> 00:24:52,699
- Draw it!
- To hell with you!

439
00:24:52,782 --> 00:24:54,534
- Screw you!
- Relax, you two!

440
00:24:54,618 --> 00:24:55,911
- I'm the traitor?!
- [Azuelo] Enough!

441
00:24:55,994 --> 00:24:56,703
[Eve] Stop this!

442
00:24:56,786 --> 00:24:57,787
Enough!

443
00:24:57,871 --> 00:24:59,497
[in English] Goddammit.

444
00:24:59,581 --> 00:25:01,708
[tense music playing]

445
00:25:03,460 --> 00:25:04,628
[suspenseful music playing]

446
00:25:04,711 --> 00:25:08,131
- Agent Marcus Reyes
- [camera shutters clicking]

447
00:25:08,215 --> 00:25:11,718
is the true protector

448
00:25:11,801 --> 00:25:17,599
of syndicate members within NLEA and SID.

449
00:25:17,682 --> 00:25:21,478
He is the son of Victor Reyes,

450
00:25:21,561 --> 00:25:25,023
the former leader of a smuggling syndicate

451
00:25:25,106 --> 00:25:29,736
who was once in cahoots with Datu Rahman

452
00:25:29,819 --> 00:25:33,865
Abubakar, or Hassan Wadi.

453
00:25:35,242 --> 00:25:40,622
Victor and Hassan were partners in crime.

454
00:25:41,623 --> 00:25:42,958
But now,

455
00:25:44,125 --> 00:25:47,462
their sons are continuing

456
00:25:48,213 --> 00:25:51,424
their plan

457
00:25:51,508 --> 00:25:54,803
to overthrow the government.

458
00:25:55,845 --> 00:26:00,558
However, they will not succeed
in their evil scheme.

459
00:26:02,227 --> 00:26:03,895
[in English] Not on my watch.

460
00:26:03,979 --> 00:26:06,273
Oh God, my sons…

461
00:26:06,940 --> 00:26:08,942
[sniffles]

462
00:26:09,025 --> 00:26:11,653
Marcus, Gabriel…

463
00:26:11,736 --> 00:26:13,947
[crying]

464
00:26:15,031 --> 00:26:16,074
Doctor…

465
00:26:16,741 --> 00:26:18,159
[sniffles]

466
00:26:18,243 --> 00:26:22,706
[in English] Marcus Reyes
and Jalil Abubakar

467
00:26:22,789 --> 00:26:25,542
are enemies of the State!

468
00:26:26,251 --> 00:26:29,462
[in English] They are armed,
and they are dangerous

469
00:26:29,546 --> 00:26:33,091
and must be neutralized on sight!

470
00:26:34,801 --> 00:26:36,678
There is a vast

471
00:26:36,761 --> 00:26:41,933
and deep conspiracy unfolding
within the police force.

472
00:26:42,684 --> 00:26:45,562
And so, I make this promise.

473
00:26:45,645 --> 00:26:51,860
To their accomplices within NLEA and SID,

474
00:26:53,403 --> 00:26:58,241
<i>you will pay for your treachery</i>

475
00:26:59,367 --> 00:27:00,785
to the Republic!

476
00:27:03,747 --> 00:27:04,581
[smacks lips]

477
00:27:09,294 --> 00:27:11,087
[laughs maniacally]

478
00:27:15,967 --> 00:27:17,886
[somber dramatic music playing]

479
00:27:17,969 --> 00:27:19,304
You're in the clear now, bro.

480
00:27:20,472 --> 00:27:22,140
But what about you?

481
00:27:22,223 --> 00:27:24,351
They'll surely come after you, too.

482
00:27:25,060 --> 00:27:26,061
That's fine.

483
00:27:26,978 --> 00:27:28,980
What matters is that
we're finally reunited.

484
00:27:29,064 --> 00:27:31,900
We will take down
General Carillo together.

485
00:27:31,983 --> 00:27:33,985
As partners.

486
00:27:34,069 --> 00:27:35,153
As comrades.

487
00:27:35,236 --> 00:27:36,279
As brothers.

488
00:27:36,363 --> 00:27:38,656
[dramatic music playing]

489
00:27:38,740 --> 00:27:39,908
Such a shame.

490
00:27:40,450 --> 00:27:43,370
Sir Mustapha's gathered evidence
would've been a big help,

491
00:27:43,453 --> 00:27:47,290
but I dropped the folder
when the bullets started flying.

492
00:27:48,124 --> 00:27:50,043
They must've taken it.

493
00:27:50,668 --> 00:27:51,503
Bro.

494
00:27:53,713 --> 00:27:55,757
The fight just got harder.

495
00:27:56,758 --> 00:27:57,801
But in the end,

496
00:27:57,884 --> 00:28:00,095
we'll still bring them down.

497
00:28:00,178 --> 00:28:02,764
[music intensifies]

498
00:28:13,274 --> 00:28:15,360
[Rustia] <i>My memories have returned, sir.</i>

499
00:28:15,443 --> 00:28:16,778
- [in English] Welcome back, Rustia.
- [Rustia sniffles]

500
00:28:16,861 --> 00:28:19,739
As long as you're in our community,
you're safe.

501
00:28:19,823 --> 00:28:22,409
[in English] The answers we are
searching for are just here.

502
00:28:22,492 --> 00:28:23,618
They're being attacked!

503
00:28:23,701 --> 00:28:29,040
I refuse to be defeated
by Marcus and Jalil!

504
00:28:30,708 --> 00:28:31,668
Mama…

505
00:28:31,751 --> 00:28:33,420
You really are my son.

506
00:28:33,503 --> 00:28:37,966
We'll never be safe, Ma,
until all of this gets sorted out.
